
#
# This file describes the prompt for the $PROMPT_NAME environment.
#
# It is a series of lines, each containing one of the following directives:
#
#   PROMPT:<prompt-string>
#     Sets the prompt to <prompt-string>.  The prompt string may contain
#     escape sequences.  The escapes are:
#
#       \w  The working directory, with $HOME abbreviated with a tilde.
#       \W  The basename of the working directory.
#       \h  The hostname up to the first '.'
#       \H  The full hostname
#       \u  The username of the current user
#       \$  If the effective UID is 0, a #, otherwise a $
#       \t  The current time in 24-hour HH:MM:SS format
#       \d
